</p>
<p>2010), pp. 9-16; Fang Gong and others, &#8220;A life course perspective on migration and mental health 
among Asian immigrants: The role of human agency&#8221;, <i>Social Science &amp; Medicine</i>, vol. 73, Iss. 11 
(2011), pp. 1618-1626. 
</p>
<p> 137  H.B.M. Murphy, &#8220;Migration, culture and mental health&#8221;, <i>Psychological Medicine,</i> vol. 7, no. 4 
(1977), pp. 677-684; D. Bhugra, &#8220;Cultural identities and cultural congruency: a new model for 
evaluating mental distress in immigrants&#8221;, <i>Acta Psychiatrica Scandinavica</i>, vol. 111, No. 2 (2005), 
pp. 84-93; Lorena de los Angeles N&#250;&#241;ez Carrasco, <i>Living on the Margins: Illness and Healthcare 
among Peruvian Migrants in Chile</i> (2008), p. 162. 
</p>
<p> 138  Yao Lu, &#8220;Household migration, social support, and psychosocial health: The perspective from 
migrant sending areas&#8221;, <i>Social Science &amp; Medicine</i>, vol. 74, Iss. 2 (January 2012), p. 141. 
</p>
